# Session log (chat capture)

At the **end of every significant session** (architecture decisions, credential setup, shipped features, debugging outcomes), append a session file under `docs/sessions/`.

## When to write

- User asks to save the chat or remember something
- A decision was made (stack, secrets, relay behavior, keys)
- Work completed or blocked with clear next steps
- Before ending a long thread

## File format

Path: `docs/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-short-slug.md`

```markdown
# Session: {title}
**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD
**Project:** dojopop | nostr-pop

## Summary
2-4 sentences.

## Decisions
- ...

## Actions taken
- ...

## Open items
- ...

## References
- Links, Doppler project names, repo paths (no secret values)
```

## Rules

- **Never** store secret values (nsec, PAT, passwords) in session files.
- Use secret **names** only (`NSEC`, `BLOSSOM_URL`).
- One file per session; update the same file if continuing the same topic same day.
- If Notion is available and user prefers cloud, offer `knowledge-capture` skill in addition to local files.

## Index

Keep `docs/sessions/README.md` table updated with new session links (newest first).

